'''Rainer Kumm''' was a German [[Rugby union|rugby player]], who played fly-half for the [[Germany national rugby union team|German national team]]<ref>100 Jahre Deutsche Rugby-Verband, Claus-Peter Bach, 2000</ref> as well as the [[Germany national rugby union team (sevens)|German Sevens team]], a team he captained in the late 1990s.

Kumm was a member of the [[Germany national rugby union team|German national team]] which toured [[Canada]] in 1988 and later competed in the erstwhile [[1996<U+2013>1997 FIRA Tournament|FIRA Tournaments]]. He was also part of the [[Germany national rugby union team (sevens)|Germany sevens squads]], which won  the Bowl final of the 1990 [[Hong Kong Sevens]], reached the Plate Final of the 1997 [[Punta Del Este Sevens]],<ref>10 anos de Seven en Punta del Este, Pedro Bordaberry, British Schools Old Boys Club, 1999</ref> won the Bowl Final of the 1997 [[Paris Sevens]], and contested the Bowl Final of the 2000 [[IRB Sevens World Series]] tournament in [[Punta Del Este Sevens|Punta del Este]]. 

He played club rugby for [[TSV Victoria Linden]] in [[Hanover]], with whom he won the [[German rugby union championship|German Championship]] in 1987, 1989, 1993, 1994 and 1996, and contested further finals in 1991, 1995, 1997, 1998 and 2000. Kumm also captained Victoria Linden to the German Sevens Championship in 2000.<ref>http://www.totalrugby.de/content/view/962/41/</ref>

After Kumm's retirement he took over from [[Gerhard Barthel]] as coach of the [[Germany national rugby union team (sevens)|Germany national sevens team]].

